==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: customs
<hw>customs</hw> <pos>n. pl.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>money collected
under a tariff; a duty imposed on imported goods.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> customs duty, custom, impost.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>the government department administering the
collection of import tariffs. Used with as singular verb.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>that area within an airport, sea port, or other
border station where freight or the baggage of travellers is checked for
dutiable materials or contraband; <as>as, it took an hour to get through
<ex>customs</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Custos</ent>⟦br⟧
